  "faqs": "Frequently asked questions",
  "faqWhatIsAppQ": "What is DueGlow?",
  "faqWhatIsAppA": "DueGlow is an app to organize beauty products, track expiration dates, and build personal care routines. It helps you keep self-care habits simple and visual.",
  "faqAddProductQ": "How do I add a product?",
  "faqAddProductA": "From the \"New\" tab you can scan a barcode, search the database, or enter details manually. You can also add products from search results or when a scan is not found in the database.",
  "faqExpirationQ": "How do expiration and PAO work?",
  "faqExpirationA": "You can set the printed expiration date or PAO (period after opening, e.g. \"6M\"). If you mark a product as opened with a date, the app can calculate when it expires from the PAO. Home shows items expiring soon.",
  "faqProductListsQ": "What are the product lists?",
  "faqProductListsA": "In \"My products\" you have several lists: items you have, wishlist, and products you finished this month. You can change the list from each product's detail screen.",
  "faqRoutinesQ": "How do I create a skincare routine?",
  "faqRoutinesA": "Go to \"Routines\", create a morning or night routine, pick the days of the week, and add products from your vanity. Home shows your next routine based on the schedule.",
  "faqScanNotFoundQ": "The scanner can't find my product — what now?",
  "faqScanNotFoundA": "If the barcode is not in the database, the app lets you create the product manually. Fill in name, brand, and expiration or PAO when possible for accurate tracking.",
  "faqExpiringSoonQ": "Where do I see products expiring soon?",
  "faqExpiringSoonA": "On the home screen, the \"Expiring Soon\" section lists products to use before they go bad. Prioritize them to avoid waste.",
  "faqSettingsLangQ": "How do I change language or theme?",
  "faqSettingsLangA": "Open \"Settings\" from the menu (three-line icon). There you can toggle notifications, choose light or dark mode, and switch between Spanish, English, and Russian.",
  "faqOpenFinishQ": "How do I mark a product as opened or finished?",
  "faqOpenFinishA": "On the product detail screen you can mark it as opened (today or another date), close it again, or mark it as finished. Finished items are recorded in your monthly usage history.",
  "faqDeleteAccountQ": "How do I delete my account?",
  "faqDeleteAccountA": "In \"Settings\", at the bottom, tap \"Delete account\". This is permanent: products, routines, images, and all linked data are removed. Only confirm if you are sure.",
